	   <tr><td colspan=2>Some of the problems with FD that I learned the hard way.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>First and foremost is not remembering to turn off the Auto Attack, that has gotten me killed many times in the early 30's.  I know monks who have a hot-key that turns off auto-attack and FD's with 1 button, as our spell can fizzle I never tried that, but it works for him.  But bottom line, if Auto-Attack is on, FD will fail.<br><br>Next, like any new spell, it will have a high failure rate till you've maxed skill and it's a few levels old.  My FD was not truely reliable till almost lvl 35.  Fizzling is related to low casting skill, &quot;falling to the ground&quot; is just like the wizard hitting for 5 with their Ice Comet spell, it's supposed to be related to the MOB seeing thru your spell.  <br><br>FD will get better with more levels and more practice.  It will still fail but much less so.  The level 60 spell Deaths Peace finally makes the spell almost fool-proof, but it's a long way off.  Just keep at the FD, it gets better.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant<br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 56 DE Revenant</td></tr>
