	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well first I'll agree with you, Sentient is one of the best armor sets for a Twink Ogre or Troll.&nbsp;&nbsp;The armor gives them the INT they need to fully exploit the Sk's strengths.  Also the best Twink Armor is not the same as the best lvl 46 Armor.  Blood Ember is great after lvl 46 when the right click effects start working, but before that it's not so great, (the legs won't click till lvl 46 so the effect is lost on the newbies).  Likewise the high AC for Blood Ember is always nice, but there are almost no other stats on them, so you loose resists, INT, STA and STR you might need based on you character early in the game.<br><br>Other nice twink armors for Ogre SKs would include Barbed Ringmail, Treeweave, Work Dragonhide (anything) or Incarnate.  Although I have never seen anyone with a full set of Incarnate, being the proud owner of the BP I'd say that might be the best Twink set available period if anyone could afford it.  The AC is very close to Blood Ember for all but the BP and the stats on it are truely awesome.  But me personally, I'm waiting to fill out my set of SS Quest Armor. ( But even when I get the SS Pants my Guild will probably have to do a Raid on me to pry away my Blood Ember Geaves :), I do love click FD even if it is slow )<br><br>Just some other thought on equipment.  Good luck.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Apr 12 09:23:31 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 56 DE Revenant</td></tr>
