	   <tr><td colspan=2>LOL--timing is all.&nbsp;&nbsp;I just posted a message a few weeks back speaking to this exact question   =)<br><br>The answer probably lies in what weapons will come into your possession, but I can tell you that, personally, I think that 1HB, 1HS &amp; 2HS are the skills that I would focus on first.  The reason for this is because there are some really nice weapons in those skills that are fairly common &amp; cheap.  2HB &amp; piercing have some nice weapons, but they just seem far harder to obtain at reasonable prices.<br><br>I think there are a few messages on this board now (heh--as of 3/29) that discuss how cheap a MoSS is (from 500 to 1k) &amp; I just saw Ebon Mace (24 dly, 19dmg) going for a really cheap 6k last nite on my server.  Both of those are 1HB. <br><br>1HS has Wurm (amongst a lot of other nice weapons), which is also very common &amp; cheap on my server, &amp; Wurm has some decent buffs too.  Graduating to a Noct Blade is also a sweet move (it&amp;#8217;s clearly better than MoSS) &amp; one was being auctioned last nite for 3k.<br><br>2HS is the SK epic (Inn's curse) &amp; also has some really nice weapons.  BABS is prob my favorite weapon at lower lvls (even with dmg caps&amp;#8212;heh)--super cheap, and has dmg per sec better than Wurm.  Strength of Grodan isn't sexy, but it has teeth.  Aged Velium Claidhmore is fun to bring into the mix also.<br><br>Sure, Shard of Night, Tantor&amp;#8217;s Tusk and Honed Velium Lance (all 1HP) are nice weapons and are all on par / better than Ebon mace, but they are like 10 times more rare &amp; expensive.  Keeping up your piercing / 2HB skill may wield some benefits, but they seem harder to realize.<br><br>If you keep those 3 skills up, I honestly believe that you won&amp;#8217;t be sorry.  Hell, even if you did somehow manage to get a really nice 2HB or piercing weapon, you can always dump a few points into the skill &amp; being it up later if you really have to.  Further, you could also sell it and get an equivalent 1HB, 1HS or 2HS as a last resort if you don&amp;#8217;t want to train in the skill.<br><br>Obviously, the best answer is to keep them all up, but if you don't want to, my recommendation is to go with those 3.<br><br>As far as wielding a 1H weapon vs a 2H weapon, pick it--your choice.  There are very strong arguments on both sides of the equation, so do what you want as far as that goes.<br><br><br>Lunatic<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
