<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101742973627818></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101742973627818><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=101742973627818>RE: Weapon Skills</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=101742973627818#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id= >lunaticfringesk</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>108 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 29th 2:26 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.15]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>ack--sorry--misread the question--<br><br>I only briefly touched the surface of the issue at hand, but wielding a 1H weapon vs a 2H weapon has compelling arguments on both sides of the fence.<br><br>Being able to use a shield (&amp; therfore wielding a 1H weapon) helps AC immensely &amp; prob inc some stats.&nbsp;&nbsp;Further, being able to bash is also a nice feature, adding dmg &amp; interrupting spell casters.<br><br>2H, on the other hand, especially after the patch that put SKs on the same dmg table as WAR &amp; also increased the dmg bonus for a 2H weapon, makes the decision very difficult to not wield a 2H weapon.  Firstly, the dmg per sec on a 2H weapon is generally higher than a 1H weapon, especially factoring in the level bonus.  Additionally, the long delay, higher dmg also is nice because, in theory, you can cast in between swings, thereby maximizing your &quot;downtime&quot; while waiting for your attack to recycle.<br><br>In general, when I am MT, I almost always wield a 1H &amp; shield to inc my ac.  When I am not MT, I generally use a 2H weapon for the inc dmg.  If I am fighting a MOB that loves to cast spells (like a complete heal, ala Spectral Curate in KC or a Umbral in SG), I will almost always wield a shield then also to potentially interrupt their casting.<br><br>At the end of the day, its a toss-up--take your pick<br><br>Lunatic<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
