	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well for your med ac gear most of it will cost more than 800pp. ie sentient bp 2500pp, darkforge leggings 1000pp.&nbsp;&nbsp;a weapon cost about 1k, i.e. wurmyslayer, MOSS..  Well at least on my server, tallon zek, being a pvp server don't know if prices are higher here.  <br><br>You could however buy an ac item that both helps your str and gear, which would be a shield.  That might be the angle you will want to go.  But your str really isn't going to matter all that much until your dmg cap is lifted after lvl 20.  Your dark reaver should be fine.  IMHO.   You could however buy a hero bracer, which helps ac and str.  Or you can buy a pair of darkforge boots and a bracer.  But 800pp isn't going to do a whole bunch.  But it's better than nothing.<br><br>I know it's not the greatest advice, but a lot depends on how you would like to play your sk.  With your mana pool I would definitly want to focus on my ac, hp, and str.  In the higher game there are str buffs from shamans, so me being a dark elf I decided to focus on full darkforge armor for the hp's (sta) and ac, at a decent price.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
